B if you will.  We range in the 30 to low 50 range, and we're not uber at all, heh.  I'm pretty much the only rogue, and want to put together a good team with some good tactics.  I don't PvP a whole lot, but i do know a little.  I practice CoD and use it ALL THE TIME no matter what i'm fighting.  I've never really tried the Joust method.  But what are some poisons i could bring to increase my chances of victory?  I know i want some Blind.  My biggest worry is the 51 enchanter that i just know will be on the other team.  What can i do about him?  Thanks all for your responses =)  LATER...<br>
<br>
-Ziele- <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uceescritdabossalini.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ceescrit da Bossalini</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/10/01 12:01:15 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Guild BoTB... need help and tactics please =)</span><hr size=1> Magic resist, poison resist and snare poison against the enchancters.  Muscle lock is THE best PvP poison for rogues in most situations.  Blind usually doesn't do you any good, unless you have a movement advantage on your opponents (lag free internet connection, SoW, small enclosed spaces, etc.).  Most smart PvP casters will keep their spells hot-keyed (especially those with shadowstep), and when a smart melee is blinded by a rogue, they will just run in circles so it will be hard to hit them with the lag monster on their side. <p><b>Ceescrit Bossalini</b><BR>
Crime Boss of Vallon Zek<BR>
{Order of the Black Rose}<BR>
---------------------------<BR><i>
"No man can separate what we create...<BR> OBR at its finest, thugs for life, assassins for hire.  Can ya feel me?  Well feel this..."</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umordier.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mordier</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/10/01 1:31:16 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Guild BoTB... need help and tactics please =)</span><hr size=1> Bossalini, nice to see the new name.  I like it.<br>
<br>
For poisons, I'd also go with those resists, or muscle lock.  If you hit him with that one and can stay on him a couple seconds he'll be hurting real bad.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubedrenkenpigsticker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bedrenken Pigsticker</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/bedrenken/halfman.jpg BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/10/01 1:35:14 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/bedrenken/bedrude.GIF WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Guild BoTB... need help and tactics please =)</span><hr size=1> Dude, get a bard in your group. They make a LOT of difference. <p>Bedrenken Pigsticker<Br>
56th level half-man bastard<br>
Povar server</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uziele.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ziele</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/10/01 3:21:19 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.egroups.com/files/HeroesofHammerHall/Dragon_Ball_One.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Guild BoTB... need help and tactics please =)</span><hr size=1> I have a bard in my guild... just one i think, lvl 36 or 37 i believe.  Don't know if he knows good PvP tactics though, what should i tell him to expect or what songs to spin?  Thanks for the info by the way...  I didn't know just how un-effective blind was aginst someone expecting it =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usgean.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sgean</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/11/01 12:16:43 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/voxton/sgean/sgean-photo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Guild BoTB... need help and tactics please =)</span><hr size=1> Great points, all -- except there's no call for poison against an enchanter. Only poison spell they cast is Tashan(i(a)) which is irresistable. <br>
<br>
Other than that, yup, all the MR you can muster (ie., a bard singing resist songs is a total must). Enchanters' spells are all magic based. <br>
<br>
Enchanters will mezz, and if you are in an arena, you can just smack them once for damage, and they wake up (or even put a SMALL dot on yourself). <br>
<br>
Yes, blind is only good in confined spaces, or places where a foe will be too scared to run blindly (due to their chances of getting killed falling off cliffs, or running into mobs etc). <br>
<br>
The key to killing a caster, is for you to be all over their ass. Their key to killing you, is to stay the hell away from you. Solution = snare or root poison. <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwiergraf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wiergraf</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/13/01 11:44:18 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Guild BoTB... need help and tactics please =)</span><hr size=1> My only advice against an enchanter would be to try and somehow avoid the nasty Flux spell. Kinda fun to be tossed up into the air, but your life bar plummets.<br>
<br>
And for your own team, I'd suggest trying to get a warrior. Useful things, they. Around 30-50, they can hit for like 250 a swing with 2Handers. <p><br>
<br>
<b>Wiergraf Deathstalker</b><br>
<i>Nero, you are an example to all the children on this shuttle. Because most of them are so foolish, they think it better to keep their stupidest thoughts to themselves. You, however, understand the profound truth that you must reveal your stupidity openly.To hold your stupidity inside you is to embrace it, to protect it. But when you expose your stupidity, you give yourself the chance to have it caught, corrected, and and replaced by wisdom. Be brave, all of you, as Nero, and when you have a thought of such surpassing ignornance that you think it's actually smart, make sure to make some noise, to let your mental limitations squeak out some whimpering fart of a thought, so that you have a chance to learn.</i>--Captain Dimak</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usterk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sterk</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/15/01 11:44:06 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Enchanter battles</span><hr size=1> I like to poison people twice--blind first (and re-coat while they stumble around) and then feeble mind or muscle lock.....if I want to see them really pissed I hit them with a Dizzy.<br>
<br>
If you use Blind II it can last long enough to coat again (God, the cleric DE's hate that) with something else...so choose and be smart.<br>
<br>
If it's a &quot;Gang Tackle&quot; fight--go with heavy MR, even in lieu of AC, and keep moving.  In my experience with these types of battles, the heavy caster usually goes for the root'n'nuke on the warriors/bards first just to take what they consider the heavy damage people out.  They love to put the rogues on the back burner--their last mistake.<br>
Keep an eye on different targets and their health levels...we're rogues--go for the big, confusing backstab while they melee/cast on someone else.  They have to watch for you now while they have someone else targeted.<br>
<br>
And always switch occasionally to a different view to make sure your back is covered.<br>
<br>
-Sterk Shadowhunter<br>
Order of the Black Rose<br>
Vallon Zek Guild Master<br>
www.eqrogue.com<br>
&quot;Stercus, E Morituris Sum <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ushariin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shariin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/16/01 10:58:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Enchanter battles</span><hr size=1> To clarify Blind; Blind is not terribly useful in a 1-on-1 duel against a caster.  When you attack them, they get you targetted, at which point they can cast their spells from memory.  OK, simple enough.<br>
<br>
